@Reasoning:
String equality helper for keyword-section detection. Wraps the dictionary's key
comparison via the list/dictionary string compare available through Dict's key
machinery is not exposed, so we reuse the lexer-independent string compare from
the layout primitive set. We compare two strings for byte equality.
@End Reasoning
Process called "lexeme_is" takes lexeme as Integer, expected as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Return 1 if lexeme equals expected (byte-for-byte)

    Return proc string_equals from StringCore with lexeme, expected
End Process
